        {
            // ... your existing firing code ...

            // Add the vibration call here with the desired intensity and duration
            VibrateController(1.0f, 0.3f); // This example will vibrate at full intensity for 0.3 seconds
        }
        else
        {
            // ... handle no ammo case ...
        }
    }
    // ... any additional code ...
}
```

Please note: The above code snippet uses preprocessor directives (like #if UNITY_STANDALONE_WIN or UNITY_XBOXONE) to ensure it only attempts to run vibration code on platforms that support it. Unity does not have a built-in `GamePad` class that supports all platforms, so you may need to use external plugins or specific APIs provided by console manufacturers to control device vibration capabilities.

Always ensure you refer to the appropriate SDK documentation or plugins for the most accurate and supported methods of implementing controller vibration for your target platform/platforms.

